        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Ok, using this code\r\n```lua\r\nlocal bufnr = 0\r\nlocal parser = vim.treesitter.get_parser(bufnr, \"c\")\r\nlocal tree = parser:parse()[1]\r\nlocal root = tree:root()\r\nlocal lang = vim.treesitter.inspect_language(\"c\")\r\nlocal query = vim.treesitter.parse_query(\"c\", \"(preproc_def)+ @test\")\r\nfor pattern, match in query:iter_matches(tree:root(), bufnr) do\r\n    for cid, node in pairs(match) do\r\n        print(node:type(), node:range())\r\n    end\r\nend\r\n```\r\n(replace the value of `bufnr` with the bufnr of something containing\r\n```c\r\n#define FOO\r\n#define BAR\r\n```\r\n)\r\nI could verify that this is indeed a problem with neovim.",
