        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "This is actually a problem with the API of `Query:iter_matches`. It returns a table a table `match` which has the capture id (`cid` in the lua code above) as its keys and the nodes as its values. But there could be multiple nodes for the same capture id, as for example if you use quantifiers in a query.\r\n\r\nI don't think that there is a backwards compatible way to resolve this. I would propose making `match` a list of `{cid, node}` pairs.",
